The paper deals with stability analysis of a random access wireless network, which is a typical problem in the field of computer networks and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis of the network, which suggests that it may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MA (Mathematical Aspects of Computer Science). The use of quasi-birth-death (QBD) processes in the modeling approach may also indicate a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.PF (Probability).
